summary: Completed comprehensive testing of MyImpact University Admin Dashboard. All core features working correctly including KPIs, verification workflows, term switching, navigation, and CSV exports.

ui_bugs.issue: KPI text includes CSS styles in text content making it hard to read
ui_bugs.description: The KPI card text content includes inline CSS styles which makes the text display cluttered

design_issues.issue: React warning about non-boolean attribute for JSX
design_issues.description: Console shows warning about jsx attribute being passed as boolean instead of string

passed_tests: Backend health check and all API endpoints (13/13 tests passed)
Dashboard loads with correct KPIs (8,432+ verified hours, 1,137 active students, 3 programs, 78% retention)
Programs panel shows 3 expected programs (Columbia Service Corps, Green Initiative, Hope NYC Outreach)
Verification requests panel shows 3 initial requests (Lily Robbins, Tai Chen, Sacha Lewiner)
Confirm participation workflow - successfully confirmed Lily Robbins request and updated KPIs
Reject workflow - successfully rejected Tai Chen request with reason selection
Flag workflow - successfully flagged Sacha Lewiner request with custom reason
Term selector functionality - switching between Spring 2026 and Fall 2025 updates programs and KPIs
Navigation between all pages (Dashboard, Activities, Participants, Reports, Admin)
Admin settings - university name change works and updates dashboard header
CSV exports - both verified logs and audit trail exports work correctly
Audit trail captures all verification actions with proper timestamps and details

success_percentage.frontend: 95% (all core functionality working, minor UI text formatting issue)
success_percentage.integration: 100% (all workflows and data flow working correctly)
